The Files
breeds.js — The database. Every breed is an object with ~12 fields: display name, sizeOrder/shedOrder/groomOrder/activeOrder (integers for comparison), coat (categorical), lifespanLow/lifespanHigh, origin, originRegion, dogCeoPath (the API path for photos), and petfinderName. It exports BREEDS (array), BREED_BY_ID (lookup by id string), and BREED_BY_NAME (lookup by lowercase name). This is what you edit when adding new breeds.

feedback.js — Pure logic, no DOM. computeFeedback(guess, target) compares two breed objects and returns an array of 7 tile objects, each with { category, value, result, arrow }. Result is "correct", "partial", or "wrong". Also exports generateShareText() which builds the emoji grid for clipboard sharing.

daily.json — The daily puzzle config. You update this every day. Fields: date (must match today or it's ignored), dogName, bio, photos (array of direct image URLs), breed1/breed2 (breed IDs from breeds.js), petfinderUrl. If this file's date doesn't match today, the game falls back to automatic breed selection.

hints.json — A flat object mapping breed ID to a hint string. Shown when the player clicks "Show Hint."

app.js — Everything else. Here's the flow:

How a Game Session Works
On load, init() runs:

Fetches daily.json — if today's date matches, sets dailyConfig and switches to multibreed mode (isMultibreed = true), sets target1 and target2
Loads saved state from localStorage (keyed by today's date like dogdle-2026-03-16) — so returning players pick up where they left off
Replays any existing guesses instantly (no animation) to restore the grid
Fetches and displays the dog photo
State object lives in memory and localStorage:


{ guesses: [...], status: 'playing'|'won'|'lost', photoUrl: null }
State is only saved for daily puzzles — bonus rounds are ephemeral.

Photo loading has two paths:

Daily puzzle with dailyConfig.photos → use those URLs directly (your Petfinder CDN photos)
Everything else (fallback daily + all bonus rounds) → call resolveDogCeoPath() which hits the dog.ceo API to find the right path, then fetches a random image from that breed's gallery
On each guess, submitGuess():

Validates the input against BREED_BY_NAME
Calls computeFeedback() to get the 7 tile results
Pushes to state.guesses, saves state
Animates the row via appendGuessRow() (tiles flip in one at a time with staggered delays)
Checks win/loss condition, then calls showModal() after 600ms
Multibreed mode (today's puzzle) is more complex — the player must find both target1 and target2. Each guess is compared against whichever remaining target it scores best against. Win = both found, loss = 8 guesses used without finding both.

The Two Modes
Daily	Bonus
isBonus	false	true
Target	From daily.json (two breeds)	Random single breed
Photo	Your CDN photos	dog.ceo random image
State saved	Yes (localStorage)	No
Counter incremented	Yes (Firebase)	No
Guesses	8	6
Bonus rounds start when the player clicks "Play Another Dog". startBonusRound() picks a random unused breed via getRandomBreed(), resets all UI state, re-enables the input, and fetches a fresh dog.ceo photo.

The New Stuff (what we just added)
Solved counter — On game complete, if !isBonus, writes true to Firebase/solved/{puzzleNum}/{sessionId}. Reading that node with ?shallow=true returns just the keys, so Object.keys(data).length = unique completions. Session ID is a UUID stored in localStorage so one player = one count even across page reloads.

Forms — Submit via POST to Formspree endpoints. Nothing is stored in your code; it goes straight to your Formspree dashboard/email.

Plausible — The script tag is on every page load. trackEvent() fires a custom "Game Complete" event with result and mode props whenever showModal() runs, so you can filter by daily vs bonus wins/losses in the Plausible dashboard.

Your Daily Workflow
To publish a new puzzle, you just edit daily.json:

Change date to today
Fill in the dog's name, bio, photo URLs, two breed IDs, and the Petfinder URL
Push to GitHub — that's it